used  to the very 'in your face' presence of several people  in  a 
small space..  One last thing to do, check to see if James Mathews 
got home, and he did, but will he be able to live down his loss of 
direction? No, he's got the Power, but not the co-ordinates!  

One  niggling  point,  there  were some weird people who  used  my 
bathroom,  as  the soapdish seemed to get filled with water,  with 
the  bit of soap therein crying for help as it slowly drowned  and 
lost  its  flavour  (no,  don't  ask!) Who was  the  mystery  soap 
drowner!!??!

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
In conclusion..
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
The  party  went  surprisingly well,  considering what is  was  up 
against..  The  main  aim was the successful launch of the  Falcon 
Maggie shell,  and this took off nicely in the time allowed.. Most 
of  the  ancillary  events took place,  although  the  total  non-
appearance  of Top Byte Software's proprietor  and  representative 
made a pigs ear of that part of the invitation..

There was a good choice of people invited, nobody ended up stabbed 
in  a  jealous frenzy by other members of the  party,  nobody  was 
mugged  for  their Falcon,  (almost) nothing blew up,  a large and 
satisfactory realtime article was written..  As far as I can tell, 
everyone  had  a good time,  most of the time at least..  The only 
area  for improvement would have been in the numbers  that  turned 
up..  Never  intended  as a huge event to start with,  it was made 
less  huge  by the lack of certain participants,  but  less  about 
James,  he  really  is starting to cry now,  every time we mention 
'Taunton!'  A  few  other  invited bodies  would  have  been  very 
welcome,  but  would  we have had people actually sleeping in  the 
bath? Probably!!

Would I do it again? - Erm, ask me that again in a while!!

